3	// eval/golden/run.js - pinned-payload diff harness.
4	//
5	// Compares every golden payload in eval/golden/goldens/<cell>.payload.json field-by-field
6	// against a fresh build output <freshDir>/<cell>.payload.json. ANY difference fails the run
7	// (exit 1) unless goldens are explicitly re-accepted with --accept.
8	//
9	// Diffs are classified for the report into the load-bearing classes:
10	//   finding-counts  (counts.*, findings lengths, frameworks lengths, rulesChecked, confirmed)
11	//   fines           (exposure*, fine*, penalty*, projected.*)
12	//   names           (company, legal_name, regulator, meta.company)
13	//   laws            (law, framework names, citation)
14	//   other           (everything else - still a failure; a golden is a golden)
15	//
16	// Usage:
17	//   node eval/golden/run.js [--fresh <dir>] [--goldens <dir>] [--accept [cell ...]] [--json]
18	//
19	// The harness FAILS CLOSED: an empty or missing goldens directory is not a pass, it is a gate that
20	// exercised no oracle, and a confident zero from a gate that compared nothing is worse than no gate
21	// (Constitution Rule 4). --accept is the single explicit bootstrap that pins the first goldens.
22	// Both filename sets are compared: a fresh cell with no pinned golden is unreviewed truth and fails
23	// until it is accepted deliberately (a golden changes only via --accept).
24	//
25	// Exit codes: 0 = every golden matches its fresh counterpart and no fresh cell is unpinned, or --accept completed;
26	//             1 = at least one diff, a golden with no fresh counterpart, an unpinned fresh cell, or no goldens at all;
27	//             2 = usage error.
